This paper is about data collection for conversational interfaces, specifically for mapping language utterances to logical forms. This topic falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP), which is covered by cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as crowdsourcing and paraphrase models, which are covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the effects of distribution mismatches, which is relevant to information retrieval (IR) and statistical learning (SD), covered by cs.IR and cs.SD respectively.
